List of maintainers
===================

alloyctl is a community-driven project: every mouse is one driver, and every
driver has a maintainer. The person who first contributes a working driver
becomes its maintainer by default (unless they explicitly hand the role to
someone else). A pull request that adds a brand-new driver MUST also add the
matching entry to this file.

This file is used to work out who should review and be assigned a pull request
that touches a given area. When you change a driver, CC or request review from
its maintainer.

Descriptions of section entries and preferred order
---------------------------------------------------

    M: *Maintainer* of this area: FullName <address@domain> (@github-handle)
       The GitHub handle is required: CI requests this person's review on any
       pull request that touches a file the section's F: patterns match.
    R: Designated *Reviewer*: FullName <address@domain> (@github-handle)
       These reviewers should also be requested on pull requests.
    S: *Status*, one of the following:
       Maintained:   Someone actually looks after it.
       Odd Fixes:    It has a maintainer but they don't have time to do
                     much other than throw the odd patch in.
       Orphan:       No current maintainer, but maybe you could take the
                     role as you write your new code.
       Obsolete:     Old code, replaced by a better system; use that instead.
    W: *Web-page* with status/info
    B: URI for where to file *bugs*, e.g. a bug tracker link or a mailto: URI.
    F: *Files* and directories wildcard patterns.
       A trailing slash includes all files and subdirectory files.
       F:    drivers/         all files in and below drivers/
       F:    drivers/*        all files in drivers/, but not below
       One pattern per line. Multiple F: lines acceptable.
    X: *Excluded* files and directories that are NOT maintained, same rules
       as F:. File exclusions are tested before file matches.

